21#include "mpc-impl.h"
22
23int
24mpc_exp (mpc_ptr rop, mpc_srcptr op, mpc_rnd_t rnd)
25{
26 mpfr_t x, y, z;
27 mpfr_prec_t prec;
28 int ok = 0;
29 int inex_re, inex_im;
30 int saved_underflow, saved_overflow;
31
32 /* special values */
33 if (mpfr_nan_p (mpc_realref (op)) || mpfr_nan_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
34 /* NaNs
35 exp(nan +i*y) = nan -i*0 if y = -0,
36 nan +i*0 if y = +0,
37 nan +i*nan otherwise
38 exp(x+i*nan) = +/-0 +/-i*0 if x=-inf,
39 +/-inf +i*nan if x=+inf,
40 nan +i*nan otherwise */
41 {
42 if (mpfr_zero_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
43 return mpc_set (rop, op, MPC_RNDNN);
44
45 if (mpfr_inf_p (mpc_realref (op)))
46 {
47 if (mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op)))
48 return mpc_set_ui_ui (rop, 0, 0, MPC_RNDNN);
49 else
50 {
51 mpfr_set_inf (mpc_realref (rop), +1);
52 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_imagref (rop));
53 return MPC_INEX(0, 0); /* Inf/NaN are exact */
54 }
55 }
56 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_realref (rop));
57 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_imagref (rop));
58 return MPC_INEX(0, 0); /* NaN is exact */
59 }
60
61
62 if (mpfr_zero_p (mpc_imagref(op)))
63 /* special case when the input is real
64 exp(x-i*0) = exp(x) -i*0, even if x is NaN
65 exp(x+i*0) = exp(x) +i*0, even if x is NaN */
66 {
67 inex_re = mpfr_exp (mpc_realref(rop), mpc_realref(op), MPC_RND_RE(rnd));
68 inex_im = mpfr_set (mpc_imagref(rop), mpc_imagref(op), MPC_RND_IM(rnd));
69 return MPC_INEX(inex_re, inex_im);
70 }
71
72 if (mpfr_zero_p (mpc_realref (op)))
73 /* special case when the input is imaginary */
74 {
75 inex_re = mpfr_cos (mpc_realref (rop), mpc_imagref (op), MPC_RND_RE(rnd));
76 inex_im = mpfr_sin (mpc_imagref (rop), mpc_imagref (op), MPC_RND_IM(rnd));
77 return MPC_INEX(inex_re, inex_im);
78 }
79
80
81 if (mpfr_inf_p (mpc_realref (op)))
82 /* real part is an infinity,
83 exp(-inf +i*y) = 0*(cos y +i*sin y)
84 exp(+inf +i*y) = +/-inf +i*nan if y = +/-inf
85 +inf*(cos y +i*sin y) if 0 < |y| < inf */
86 {
87 mpfr_t n;
88
89 mpfr_init2 (n, 2);
90 if (mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op)))
91 mpfr_set_ui (n, 0, MPFR_RNDN);
92 else
93 mpfr_set_inf (n, +1);
94
95 if (mpfr_inf_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
96 {
97 int real_sign = mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op));
98 inex_re = mpfr_set (mpc_realref (rop), n, MPFR_RNDN);
99 if (real_sign)
100 inex_im = mpfr_set (mpc_imagref (rop), n, MPFR_RNDN);
101 else
102 {
103 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_imagref (rop));
104 inex_im = 0; /* NaN is exact */
105 }
106 }
107 else
108 {
109 mpfr_t c, s;
110 mpfr_init2 (c, 2);
111 mpfr_init2 (s, 2);
112
113 mpfr_sin_cos (s, c, mpc_imagref (op), MPFR_RNDN);
114 inex_re = mpfr_copysign (mpc_realref (rop), n, c, MPFR_RNDN);
115 inex_im = mpfr_copysign (mpc_imagref (rop), n, s, MPFR_RNDN);
116
117 mpfr_clear (s);
118 mpfr_clear (c);
119 }
120
121 mpfr_clear (n);
122 return MPC_INEX(inex_re, inex_im);
123 }
124
125 if (mpfr_inf_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
126 /* real part is finite non-zero number, imaginary part is an infinity */
127 {
128 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_realref (rop));
129 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_imagref (rop));
130 return MPC_INEX(0, 0); /* NaN is exact */
131 }
132
133
134 /* from now on, both parts of op are regular numbers */
135
136 prec = MPC_MAX_PREC(rop)
137 + MPC_MAX (MPC_MAX (-mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref (op)), 0),
138 -mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref (op)));
139 /* When op is close to 0, then exp is close to 1+Re(op), while
140 cos is close to 1-Im(op); to decide on the ternary value of exp*cos,
141 we need a high enough precision so that none of exp or cos is
142 computed as 1. */
143 mpfr_init2 (x, 2);
144 mpfr_init2 (y, 2);
145 mpfr_init2 (z, 2);
146
147 /* save the underflow or overflow flags from MPFR */
148 saved_underflow = mpfr_underflow_p ();
149 saved_overflow = mpfr_overflow_p ();
150
151 do
152 {
153 prec += mpc_ceil_log2 (prec) + 5;
154
155 mpfr_set_prec (x, prec);
156 mpfr_set_prec (y, prec);
157 mpfr_set_prec (z, prec);
158
159 /* FIXME: x may overflow so x.y does overflow too, while Re(exp(op))
160 could be represented in the precision of rop. */
161 mpfr_clear_overflow ();
162 mpfr_clear_underflow ();
163 mpfr_exp (x, mpc_realref(op), MPFR_RNDN); /* error <= 0.5ulp */
164 mpfr_sin_cos (z, y, mpc_imagref(op), MPFR_RNDN); /* errors <= 0.5ulp */
165 mpfr_mul (y, y, x, MPFR_RNDN); /* error <= 2ulp */
166 ok = mpfr_overflow_p () || mpfr_zero_p (x)
167 || mpfr_can_round (y, prec - 2, MPFR_RNDN, MPFR_RNDZ,
168 MPC_PREC_RE(rop) + (MPC_RND_RE(rnd) == MPFR_RNDN));
169 if (ok) /* compute imaginary part */
170 {
171 mpfr_mul (z, z, x, MPFR_RNDN);
172 ok = mpfr_overflow_p () || mpfr_zero_p (x)
173 || mpfr_can_round (z, prec - 2, MPFR_RNDN, MPFR_RNDZ,
174 MPC_PREC_IM(rop) + (MPC_RND_IM(rnd) == MPFR_RNDN));
175 }
176 }
177 while (ok == 0);
178
179 inex_re = mpfr_set (mpc_realref(rop), y, MPC_RND_RE(rnd));
180 inex_im = mpfr_set (mpc_imagref(rop), z, MPC_RND_IM(rnd));
181 if (mpfr_overflow_p ())
182 {
183 inex_re = mpc_fix_inf (mpc_realref(rop), MPC_RND_RE(rnd));
184 inex_im = mpc_fix_inf (mpc_imagref(rop), MPC_RND_IM(rnd));
185 }
186 else if (mpfr_underflow_p ())
187 {
188 inex_re = mpc_fix_zero (mpc_realref(rop), MPC_RND_RE(rnd));
189 inex_im = mpc_fix_zero (mpc_imagref(rop), MPC_RND_IM(rnd));
190 }
191
192 mpfr_clear (x);
193 mpfr_clear (y);
194 mpfr_clear (z);
195
196 /* restore underflow and overflow flags from MPFR */
197 if (saved_underflow)
198 mpfr_set_underflow ();
199 if (saved_overflow)
200 mpfr_set_overflow ();
201
202 return MPC_INEX(inex_re, inex_im);
203}
